WEBVTT

00:04.005 --> 00:10.943
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:22.757 --> 00:24.390
- Switching over
to night vision.

00:24.425 --> 00:26.625
- Make sure to check
your K-2 meter.

00:26.660 --> 00:28.560
It's working?
[meter beeps]

00:28.596 --> 00:35.567
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:35.603 --> 00:37.970
[meter beeping]
- Picking something up.

00:38.005 --> 00:40.606
[meter beeps rapidly]

00:40.641 --> 00:41.607
- What is it?

00:49.386 --> 00:50.819
- Uhh!
- Guys, cut it out!

00:50.854 --> 00:52.454
I don't like this.
- [screams]

00:52.489 --> 00:54.756
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:54.792 --> 00:55.991
- [gasping]

00:56.026 --> 00:57.893
- I'm bleeding!

00:57.928 --> 01:00.295
- [screams]

01:00.331 --> 01:03.298
<i> [haunting music]</i>

01:03.334 --> 01:10.272
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:29.093 --> 01:32.127
<i> - After I graduated,</i>
<i> I went into the military.</i>

01:32.162 --> 01:34.997
I was part of
Desert Shield/Desert Storm.

01:35.032 --> 01:37.499
Did about six months
in Saudi Arabia and Iraq.

01:37.534 --> 01:39.735
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:39.770 --> 01:41.403
<i> After I left the military,</i>

01:41.438 --> 01:43.705
I started working at South
Pittsburgh Municipal Hospital

01:43.741 --> 01:45.107
in Tennessee.

01:45.142 --> 01:48.310
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:48.345 --> 01:49.945
The only downside
to the job was,

01:49.980 --> 01:52.314
I had to work the night shift--

01:52.349 --> 01:55.450
<i> from 11:00 p.m. at night</i>
<i> to 7:00 a.m. in the morning,</i>

01:55.486 --> 01:56.585
the graveyard shift.

01:56.620 --> 01:58.687
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:58.722 --> 02:00.222
- Hey, Cheryl.
- Hey, Don.

02:00.257 --> 02:01.223
- How's your night going?

02:01.258 --> 02:03.392
- Good.
It's good.

02:03.427 --> 02:05.193
- South Pittsburgh
Municipal Hospital

02:05.229 --> 02:10.232
was built in the late '50s,
I think around 1959.

02:10.267 --> 02:13.635
I worked in the clinical lab,
which is on the second floor.

02:13.671 --> 02:17.472
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:17.508 --> 02:19.474
I worked with blood,
and part of my job

02:19.510 --> 02:23.745
<i> was to collect blood samples</i>
<i> and do the testing.</i>

02:23.781 --> 02:28.050
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:28.085 --> 02:29.584
<i> Put the blood</i>
<i> in the centrifuge.</i>

02:29.620 --> 02:30.752
<i> It spins it down.</i>

02:30.788 --> 02:33.855
And then I started up
the analyzers.

02:33.891 --> 02:36.825
[centrifuge whirring]

02:48.572 --> 02:50.472
[glass shatters]

02:50.507 --> 02:53.308
And there, sitting in the middle
of the floor,

02:53.343 --> 02:55.577
<i> is a test tube.</i>

02:55.612 --> 02:57.446
I can't explain
how it could have fallen

02:57.481 --> 03:00.082
off the refrigerator.

03:00.117 --> 03:01.917
<i> It's almost like</i>
<i> someone had picked it up</i>

03:01.952 --> 03:04.886
<i> and just carelessly</i>
<i> dropped it on the floor.</i>

03:06.890 --> 03:08.657
So my first thought was, "Okay,

03:08.692 --> 03:10.459
somebody is pulling a prank
on me."

03:14.164 --> 03:15.330
- Kev!

03:15.365 --> 03:16.765
<i> - I worked with this guy</i>
<i> named Kevin.</i>

03:16.800 --> 03:18.800
He worked over in X-ray,
and he was a prankster.

03:18.836 --> 03:21.403
- Was that you?
- What are you talking about?

03:21.438 --> 03:22.838
- I said, "Look,"

03:22.873 --> 03:24.473
and I point at the test tubes
on the floor.

03:24.508 --> 03:25.874
And he says, "What about it?"

03:25.909 --> 03:26.908
<i> And I said...</i>

03:26.944 --> 03:28.610
- Did you do that?

03:28.645 --> 03:30.178
- You think I did it?

03:30.214 --> 03:31.880
- And I said,
"I didn't do that."

03:31.915 --> 03:34.583
And he kind of gave me
a look like...

03:34.618 --> 03:37.519
- Come on, y'all are messing
with me with that.

03:37.554 --> 03:39.454
- You need to get some sleep.

03:39.490 --> 03:42.657
<i>- And there was no one in there</i>
<i> but me.</i>

03:42.693 --> 03:49.664
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:49.700 --> 03:52.667
<i> [ominous music]</i>

03:52.703 --> 03:59.641
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:02.179 --> 04:03.278
It was getting late.

04:03.313 --> 04:04.946
It's about 2:00,
3:00 in the morning.

04:04.982 --> 04:06.815
[soft country music playing]

04:06.850 --> 04:08.216
<i> - ♪ I remember... ♪</i>

04:08.252 --> 04:09.651
- I was getting
a little bit sleepy,

04:09.686 --> 04:10.886
so I thought I would go down
and get a cup of coffee.

04:10.921 --> 04:13.889
<i> [ominous music]</i>

04:13.924 --> 04:16.825
- [sighs]

04:16.860 --> 04:18.260
<i> So I went around</i>
<i> to the elevator.</i>

04:18.295 --> 04:19.995
<i> The elevator was near</i>
<i> the nurses' station.</i>

04:20.030 --> 04:21.830
<i> And I hit the button, and...</i>

04:21.865 --> 04:24.533
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:24.568 --> 04:26.234
Nothing.

04:26.270 --> 04:28.503
[button clicking]

04:28.539 --> 04:32.307
<i> And I waited, and I waited,</i>
<i> and...</i>

04:32.342 --> 04:33.975
totally nothing.

04:34.011 --> 04:36.478
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:36.513 --> 04:37.712
So I thought, you know,

04:37.748 --> 04:39.214
"I'm not gonna wait
on this elevator.

04:39.249 --> 04:41.249
<i> I'm just gonna go on down."</i>

04:46.890 --> 04:50.192
<i> I got down to about--</i>
<i>about halfway down the hallway.</i>

04:50.227 --> 04:53.161
[elevator machinery whirring]

04:56.900 --> 04:58.466
You could hear
the motor running.

04:58.502 --> 05:00.135
You could hear the movement.

05:00.170 --> 05:04.372
[elevator whirs and clangs]

05:04.408 --> 05:05.740
I heard the door kind of, "Eee!"

05:09.580 --> 05:11.279
<i> And no one was there.</i>

05:12.749 --> 05:14.616
<i> I didn't think anything</i>
<i> about it at the time.</i>

05:14.651 --> 05:16.518
<i> I thought somebody had</i>
<i> just changed their mind,</i>

05:16.553 --> 05:17.786
or maybe they got called away.

05:17.821 --> 05:19.120
I just didn't think much
about it.

05:32.236 --> 05:35.604
A few weeks later, it was
about 4:30 in the morning.

05:35.639 --> 05:38.106
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:38.141 --> 05:40.041
<i> Kevin came in.</i>

05:40.077 --> 05:42.878
- Don, there's a new lab tech
coming in.

05:42.913 --> 05:44.145
His name is Tony.

05:44.181 --> 05:46.147
He'll be here around about
4:00 or 5:00.

05:46.183 --> 05:47.916
Uh, when he gets here, do you
want to just show him around,

05:47.951 --> 05:49.084
make him feel welcome?

05:49.119 --> 05:50.151
- Sure, no problem.
- Yeah?

05:50.187 --> 05:51.820
- Happy to help.

05:54.691 --> 06:00.829
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:00.864 --> 06:03.965
<i> - I'd been out</i>
<i> collecting blood.</i>

06:04.001 --> 06:05.066
As I turn the corner,

06:05.102 --> 06:07.168
I see a guy sitting
on a couch.

06:09.673 --> 06:12.874
- Hey, you must be Tony.

06:12.910 --> 06:14.843
Hang--hang on a second.
I'll be right with you.

06:14.878 --> 06:17.178
<i> - He had kind of sandy blond</i>
<i> hair, about shoulder length.</i>

06:17.214 --> 06:19.214
<i> He had a thin beard.</i>

06:19.249 --> 06:21.049
- Little earlier
than I thought you--

06:21.084 --> 06:25.153
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:25.188 --> 06:27.122
- Nobody's there.

06:27.157 --> 06:28.623
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:28.659 --> 06:30.325
I mean, he was
right in front of me,

06:30.360 --> 06:31.526
and now he's gone.

06:31.561 --> 06:33.128
I mean, I just turned around
for a second,

06:33.163 --> 06:34.663
and he's gone.

06:34.698 --> 06:37.399
- Hey.

06:37.434 --> 06:40.669
<i> - There's a guy</i>
<i> had on blue scrubs.</i>

06:40.704 --> 06:42.871
- How's it going?
I'm Tony.

06:42.906 --> 06:44.572
- He said, "Hi.
My name's Tony."

06:44.608 --> 06:47.375
- You're the new guy?
- Yeah.

06:47.411 --> 06:48.910
- Uh, Don.
- Yeah.

06:48.946 --> 06:52.447
- Nice to meet you.
Um...yeah.

06:52.482 --> 06:53.682
<i> - I didn't mention it.</i>

06:53.717 --> 06:55.650
<i> I just said,</i>
<i> "Hey, good to meet you,"</i>

06:55.686 --> 06:57.652
because what am I
gonna tell him?

06:57.688 --> 07:00.822
<i> I was nervous.</i>

07:00.857 --> 07:02.590
- Something wrong?

07:02.626 --> 07:06.227
- No, I...
saw something.

07:06.263 --> 07:07.996
- Either there's something
I can't explain,

07:08.031 --> 07:09.864
or I'm just, you know,
completely crazy.

07:09.900 --> 07:15.437
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:15.472 --> 07:17.205
- I honestly don't remember

07:17.240 --> 07:19.641
having so many samples
in one week.

07:19.676 --> 07:21.676
- I can only imagine.

07:21.712 --> 07:23.345
-<i> One particular night,</i>

07:23.380 --> 07:25.714
<i> I was kind of hanging out</i>
<i> with this guy, Matthew,</i>

07:25.749 --> 07:27.482
close to the nurses' station.

07:29.086 --> 07:30.385
- Thinking about going up
to Lake Barkley.

07:30.420 --> 07:32.053
Have you ever been up there?
- Oh, yeah.

07:32.089 --> 07:34.356
Pretty nice spot.
- Some good fishing.

07:34.391 --> 07:37.292
- Great. It really is.
<i> [distant wail]</i>

07:37.327 --> 07:39.127
- It almost sounded like
a cat meowing,

07:39.162 --> 07:41.563
but it was like, "Rrrrrr."

07:41.598 --> 07:44.566
<i> [distant wail]</i>

07:44.601 --> 07:47.635
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:47.671 --> 07:50.805
<i> [baby crying]</i>

07:50.841 --> 07:51.940
<i> And then we got to listening,</i>

07:51.975 --> 07:54.009
and it wasn't a cat,
it was a baby.

07:54.044 --> 07:57.078
<i> [baby crying]</i>

07:57.114 --> 07:58.980
- You hear that?
<i> [babies crying]</i>

07:59.016 --> 07:59.981
- I think so.

08:00.017 --> 08:01.916
- It was more than one baby.

08:01.952 --> 08:04.452
It sounded like a room full
of babies screaming.

08:04.488 --> 08:07.455
<i> [babies crying]</i>

08:07.491 --> 08:10.158
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:10.193 --> 08:12.460
- Hold--hold on.
Listen.

08:12.496 --> 08:15.797
<i> - And you could hear it</i>
<i> coming through that door.</i>

08:15.832 --> 08:17.298
<i> [babies crying]</i>

08:17.334 --> 08:19.334
<i> I tried the handle</i>
<i> in the office.</i>

08:19.369 --> 08:22.404
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

08:22.439 --> 08:24.706
<i> [silence]</i>

08:24.741 --> 08:26.641
<i> But the door was locked.</i>

08:26.676 --> 08:27.809
- It stopped.

08:27.844 --> 08:29.277
<i> - At the time</i>
<i> I was working there,</i>

08:29.312 --> 08:31.513
they didn't deliver babies
at that hospital,

08:31.548 --> 08:33.815
<i> but Kevin said</i>
<i> that used to be Maternity</i>

08:33.850 --> 08:34.849
back in the day.

08:34.885 --> 08:36.117
And I said, "What do you mean?"

08:36.153 --> 08:39.421
He said, "That's where
the nursery was."

08:39.456 --> 08:41.056
- I really need a vacation.

08:41.091 --> 08:42.157
- I hear that one, boy.

08:42.192 --> 08:49.130
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:57.074 --> 09:00.975
<i> - I've got this test</i>
<i> I'm having to do.</i>

09:01.011 --> 09:05.046
<i> I had to put a patient sample</i>
<i> in the kit.</i>

09:05.082 --> 09:06.848
And you had to watch
to make sure

09:06.883 --> 09:09.150
that the sample absorbed
into the kit.

09:09.186 --> 09:16.124
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:33.643 --> 09:35.343
Out of the corner of my eye,
I saw a little bit of movement.

09:35.378 --> 09:41.049
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:41.084 --> 09:44.853
<i> I could see two shadows</i>
<i> on the wall--</i>

09:44.888 --> 09:48.890
my shadow, and then right near
to my shadow was another shadow.

09:48.925 --> 09:50.692
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:50.727 --> 09:55.663
- [growling]

09:55.699 --> 09:57.699
[roars]

09:57.734 --> 09:59.067
<i> - And there was nobody</i>
<i> in the lab.</i>

09:59.102 --> 10:06.007
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:06.042 --> 10:08.309
<i> I can't explain this.</i>

10:08.345 --> 10:09.844
I don't know how
to explain this.

10:09.880 --> 10:12.981
<i> I was really anxious</i>
<i> to get out of there.</i>

10:13.016 --> 10:15.950
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:15.986 --> 10:17.185
That night scared me.

10:17.220 --> 10:23.491
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:23.527 --> 10:25.693
<i> After that night,</i>

10:25.729 --> 10:27.328
got an opportunity
to go somewhere else,

10:27.364 --> 10:28.596
and I took it.

10:28.632 --> 10:35.570
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:39.242 --> 10:41.476
<i> [whispered voices]</i>

10:41.511 --> 10:43.845
<i> - Oh, my God, I'm bleeding.</i>

10:43.880 --> 10:45.013
<i> - [screams]</i>

10:52.856 --> 10:55.890
<i> [ominous music]</i>

10:55.926 --> 11:02.897
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:02.933 --> 11:04.999
<i> - My father-in-law bought</i>

11:05.035 --> 11:08.102
<i> the old South Pittsburgh</i>
<i> hospital.</i>

11:08.138 --> 11:10.138
The hospital had been abandoned
for several years.

11:10.173 --> 11:11.940
It had fallen into
a state of disrepair,

11:11.975 --> 11:14.475
and he was able to get it
for a really good price.

11:14.511 --> 11:17.812
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:17.847 --> 11:23.051
<i> He decided to turn it</i>
<i> into a storage facility.</i>

11:23.086 --> 11:26.254
I became the general manager/
caretaker of the property.

11:26.289 --> 11:30.291
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:30.327 --> 11:33.962
<i> The first time I ever walked</i>
<i> into the building,</i>

11:33.997 --> 11:37.165
<i> it was very creepy.</i>

11:37.200 --> 11:38.366
[door closes]

11:45.275 --> 11:47.575
[birds flap loudly]

12:04.294 --> 12:06.594
<i> [haunting music]</i>

12:06.630 --> 12:08.796
<i> There was lots of beds</i>
<i> all over the place.</i>

12:08.832 --> 12:11.899
<i> There was wheelchairs</i>
<i> everywhere.</i>

12:11.935 --> 12:14.569
<i> Lots of trash everywhere.</i>

12:14.604 --> 12:20.541
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:22.812 --> 12:25.480
<i>The place had a strange feeling</i>
<i> about it.</i>

12:25.515 --> 12:27.348
And I just have to keep
telling myself,

12:27.384 --> 12:28.883
"This is just a building.

12:28.918 --> 12:30.918
<i> "That's all it is.</i>

12:30.954 --> 12:33.288
<i> It's just an old building."</i>

12:37.794 --> 12:39.627
[plastic crunches]

12:42.699 --> 12:49.637
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:55.278 --> 12:56.911
I worked really, really hard

12:56.946 --> 12:58.413
for a couple of weeks
in the building

12:58.448 --> 13:02.083
to get all the debris out,
equipment moved.

13:02.118 --> 13:04.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:04.587 --> 13:05.553
- Watch your step there.

13:05.588 --> 13:07.355
Can you manage?
- Yeah.

13:07.390 --> 13:10.258
<i>- One afternoon, Charles and I,</i>
<i> who's one of our workers,</i>

13:10.293 --> 13:11.993
we were downstairs,
going through

13:12.028 --> 13:14.829
<i> all these boxes</i>
<i> that we had found.</i>

13:14.864 --> 13:16.331
- So how's your dad doing?

13:16.366 --> 13:17.699
- He's doing really well,
actually.

13:17.734 --> 13:19.767
- That's good to hear.

13:19.803 --> 13:21.869
- We're busy working away,
and all of a sudden...

13:21.905 --> 13:24.138
<i> [telephone rings]</i>

13:24.174 --> 13:26.441
<i> We hear this phone ringing.</i>

13:26.476 --> 13:29.444
<i> [ringing continues]</i>

13:29.479 --> 13:30.478
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:30.513 --> 13:32.680
<i> But then it hits me.</i>

13:32.716 --> 13:34.482
There's no phones there.

13:34.517 --> 13:36.250
There's none in the building.

13:36.286 --> 13:37.385
They're all gone.

13:37.420 --> 13:40.388
<i> [phone ringing]</i>

13:40.423 --> 13:45.593
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:45.628 --> 13:47.962
And I'm like, "Where is this
coming from?"

13:47.997 --> 13:50.965
<i> [phone ringing loudly]</i>

13:51.000 --> 13:57.939
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:59.175 --> 14:00.508
<i> It's just the old wires</i>

14:00.543 --> 14:03.778
<i> that are hanging</i>
<i> out of the wall.</i>

14:03.813 --> 14:06.547
I have no explanation
where that phone was ringing at,

14:06.583 --> 14:11.119
because they had all been
turned off and disconnected.

14:11.154 --> 14:13.221
- Let's get back.

14:13.256 --> 14:16.190
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:16.226 --> 14:19.994
<i> - Actually,</i>
<i> to be honest about it,</i>

14:20.029 --> 14:21.596
it scared the hell out of me.

14:21.631 --> 14:25.133
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:33.977 --> 14:36.210
<i>If you're there all by yourself</i>

14:36.246 --> 14:37.812
and working by yourself,

14:37.847 --> 14:42.116
<i> it's very easy to get spooked</i>
<i> in that building.</i>

14:42.152 --> 14:44.218
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:44.254 --> 14:45.686
<i> [faint whooshing]</i>

14:45.722 --> 14:47.755
All of a sudden,
I hear this sound.

14:47.791 --> 14:50.258
It's like a "whoosh" sound.

14:50.293 --> 14:54.028
<i> So I stop what I'm doing,</i>
<i> and I walk around the corner.</i>

14:54.063 --> 15:01.002
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:10.013 --> 15:12.447
<i> And I happen to look up,</i>

15:12.482 --> 15:16.117
and it was where a curtain
used to be.

15:16.152 --> 15:18.820
<i> The hooks were moving.</i>

15:18.855 --> 15:20.321
<i> They're swinging.</i>

15:20.356 --> 15:21.956
They're just back and forth.

15:21.991 --> 15:26.093
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:26.129 --> 15:27.528
There's no wind.

15:27.564 --> 15:30.364
<i> No windows are open.</i>

15:30.400 --> 15:31.999
<i> [dramatic music hit]</i>

15:32.035 --> 15:35.002
<i> [tense music]</i>

15:35.038 --> 15:36.704
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:36.739 --> 15:39.707
<i> I can't explain this.</i>

15:39.742 --> 15:45.480
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:45.515 --> 15:47.982
I could not make sense
out of what was going on.

15:48.017 --> 15:49.550
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:49.586 --> 15:51.519
<i> But I was so busy and consumed</i>

15:51.554 --> 15:52.687
<i> in doing what I was doing</i>

15:52.722 --> 15:55.656
<i> that I just kept working.</i>

16:00.630 --> 16:03.564
It started to get really cold.
The temperature dropped.

16:03.600 --> 16:07.702
<i> And as I'm walking</i>
<i> around the corner,</i>

16:07.737 --> 16:10.404
I stopped dead in my tracks.

16:10.440 --> 16:14.242
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:14.277 --> 16:17.044
<i> I notice there's a puddle</i>
