18:23.906 --> 18:25.706
<i> My name is Stacey.</i>

18:25.742 --> 18:27.475
- She explained
that her name was Stacey

18:27.510 --> 18:31.345
and that she ran a hospital
in South Pittsburgh, Tennessee.

18:31.381 --> 18:34.682
There was something that had
absolutely shaken her

18:34.717 --> 18:35.783
to her core.

18:35.818 --> 18:37.551
- I'll get back to you, Stacey.

18:37.587 --> 18:41.422
<i> - She needed help.</i>

18:41.457 --> 18:44.692
It is absolutely essential
to do background research

18:44.727 --> 18:47.628
and to know
what you are walking into.

18:47.664 --> 18:51.365
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:51.401 --> 18:54.468
I type in "South Pittsburgh
Municipal Hospital,"

18:54.504 --> 18:55.870
and all of a sudden,

18:55.905 --> 18:58.673
all these stories
start popping up--

18:58.708 --> 19:01.175
<i> patients that have died there,</i>

19:01.210 --> 19:05.046
how babies were not
taken care of.

19:05.081 --> 19:08.049
<i> There was</i>
<i> a high mortality rate.</i>

19:08.084 --> 19:11.052
<i> There's so many</i>
<i> different layers and stories</i>

19:11.087 --> 19:16.190
to the hospital
that I was blown away.

19:16.225 --> 19:17.992
If I was going to find out
what was going on,

19:18.027 --> 19:20.094
I needed to see it
with my own eyes.

19:20.129 --> 19:23.330
<i> We were going to have to put</i>
<i> a team together.</i>

19:23.366 --> 19:29.070
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:29.105 --> 19:31.939
- Rolling.
Tape ID: Day one

19:31.974 --> 19:35.743
of South Pittsburgh Municipal
Hospital investigation.

19:35.778 --> 19:37.078
I see them.

19:37.113 --> 19:39.213
Oh, there's the rest
of the team there.

19:39.248 --> 19:40.715
Looking good.
All right.

19:40.750 --> 19:41.982
So we're gonna spend
two nights here

19:42.018 --> 19:45.152
and set up our equipment,
and see if we can catch

19:45.188 --> 19:47.188
her son-of-a-gun...
[indistinct]

19:47.223 --> 19:48.289
See what's going on.
Hey.

19:48.324 --> 19:49.924
How you feeling there, Jenn?

19:49.959 --> 19:52.326
- [chuckles]
I'm a little nervous.

19:52.361 --> 19:53.794
- Oh, it's gonna be all right.

19:53.830 --> 19:55.763
I'll be right beside you.
All right.

19:55.798 --> 19:59.600
Let's go and meet the rest
of the team here.

19:59.635 --> 20:01.402
See what's going on.

20:01.437 --> 20:03.170
- I've been with
Shannon's paranormal group

20:03.206 --> 20:05.940
for about 2 1/2 years now.

20:05.975 --> 20:07.842
<i> You know, I'm one of those</i>

20:07.877 --> 20:10.077
<i> that always has a camera</i>
<i> in my hand.</i>

20:10.113 --> 20:12.613
- All righty,
it's about 8:15,

20:12.648 --> 20:15.983
and we're here at
the South Pittsburgh Hospital.

20:16.018 --> 20:18.152
- I want to catch
what's fixing to happen.

20:18.187 --> 20:19.754
- This is the rest
of the team behind me.

20:19.789 --> 20:22.556
Let's see how they're doing.

20:22.592 --> 20:24.625
- Doing these investigations
do give me a rush.

20:24.660 --> 20:26.794
- This is Jennifer.
She's new.

20:26.829 --> 20:28.596
Say hi, Jenn.
- Hi.

20:28.631 --> 20:31.866
- I had never in my life
been on an investigation,

20:31.901 --> 20:34.335
and this was my very first one.

20:34.370 --> 20:36.337
- Yeah, that's Robin over there.

20:36.372 --> 20:37.338
She's a medium.
- Hi.

20:37.373 --> 20:38.906
<i> - I am a medium,</i>

20:38.941 --> 20:44.378
but I am also the historian
and an investigator.

20:44.413 --> 20:46.547
<i>Shannon didn't tell me anything</i>
<i> about the place.</i>

20:46.582 --> 20:49.784
She wanted me to experience
everything firsthand.

20:49.819 --> 20:52.686
<i> I was excited about it.</i>

20:52.722 --> 20:55.222
- And there you are.
Over here is Big Shane.

20:55.258 --> 20:58.893
He's our tech guy.
How's it going, Shane?

20:58.928 --> 20:59.894
Okay.

20:59.929 --> 21:01.362
<i> - I'm the tech guy.</i>

21:01.397 --> 21:02.696
I make sure
everything we capture

21:02.732 --> 21:03.864
is recorded and everything,

21:03.900 --> 21:05.566
make sure the camera
is working properly,

21:05.601 --> 21:06.934
recorders are working properly.

21:06.969 --> 21:10.771
<i> The hospital seemed</i>
<i> very intriguing to me.</i>

21:10.807 --> 21:12.807
I just--I couldn't wait
to get in there

21:12.842 --> 21:14.208
and see what we could find out.

21:14.243 --> 21:17.845
- And last but not least
is our fearless leader Shannon.

21:17.880 --> 21:20.114
- Cody, can you stop that
and give us a hand?

21:20.149 --> 21:22.149
Come on.

21:24.253 --> 21:26.654
This is Jennifer.
- Hi.

21:26.689 --> 21:31.292
-<i> I met the paranormal group</i>
<i> just outside of the hospital.</i>

21:31.327 --> 21:34.662
They wanted me to come in and
show them around the building,

21:34.697 --> 21:37.398
but I told them no, that I was
not going back in there

21:37.433 --> 21:39.533
until I knew what was going on.

21:47.210 --> 21:49.343
- You all right?
- Yeah.

21:53.850 --> 21:55.249
- Setting up base camp.

21:55.284 --> 21:56.784
Everybody's doing a good job.

21:56.819 --> 21:58.953
Let's see what they're up to.

21:58.988 --> 22:00.621
Okay, there's Shane.

22:00.656 --> 22:03.290
Shane set up the generator
so we got some lights working.

22:03.326 --> 22:06.861
- We set up base camp
at the nurses' station

22:06.896 --> 22:08.762
on the second floor
of the hospital.

22:12.468 --> 22:13.734
- Hey, Robin,
you getting in the zone?

22:13.769 --> 22:16.670
- Shh!
Now now, Cody.

22:16.706 --> 22:20.174
I need quiet.
- Sorry.

22:20.209 --> 22:21.609
Look at this place.

22:21.644 --> 22:23.344
So dirty.

22:23.379 --> 22:25.813
We don't have to clean it up.

22:25.848 --> 22:28.015
And then through here is Jenn.

22:28.050 --> 22:31.518
Jenn is working on a little bit
of a rest area for the time.

22:31.554 --> 22:33.354
Hi, Jenn.
- Hey.

22:33.389 --> 22:37.291
- We had sleeping bags, water,
flashlights, spare batteries.

22:37.326 --> 22:38.759
You know, we were here
for the whole nine yards.

22:38.794 --> 22:40.995
- Remember,
make mine extra comfy

22:41.030 --> 22:43.931
and far away from Shane's.

22:43.966 --> 22:46.934
You got any of those mints
you can leave on the pillows?

22:46.969 --> 22:49.770
- I'll see what I can do.
- Thanks, Jenn.

22:49.805 --> 22:51.805
- We had six cameras,
and I set them up

22:51.841 --> 22:54.341
at different vantage points
throughout the whole hospital--

22:54.377 --> 22:58.746
<i> third floor, the basement,</i>
<i> different corridors...</i>

23:01.484 --> 23:04.351
<i> ICU, the emergency room.</i>

23:09.892 --> 23:11.091
<i> I just wanted to make sure</i>

23:11.127 --> 23:12.726
I had the whole building covered
with cameras.

23:29.078 --> 23:31.912
- Guys, kill the lights.

23:34.583 --> 23:36.750
- Switching over
to night vision.

23:36.786 --> 23:38.786
- Make sure to check
your K-2 meter.

23:38.821 --> 23:40.187
[meter beeping]
Is it working?

23:40.222 --> 23:44.858
- A K-2 meter essentially looks
for alterations

23:44.894 --> 23:47.795
in the electromagnetic field.

23:47.830 --> 23:50.264
- Any changes in the EMF field
could signify

23:50.299 --> 23:52.066
the presence of a spirit.

23:52.101 --> 23:55.703
- Are we ready?
Check the cameras?

23:55.738 --> 23:57.938
- The last thing Shannon said
was, "Stay together,

23:57.974 --> 23:59.406
and keep your radios on."

23:59.442 --> 24:00.808
[radio static]

24:00.843 --> 24:04.678
- Let's do this, guys.

24:04.714 --> 24:07.815
<i> - We began our initial sweep</i>
<i> of the hospital.</i>

24:16.258 --> 24:17.858
<i> - We left base camp,</i>

24:17.893 --> 24:20.627
<i> and we started to move</i>
<i> across the second floor.</i>

24:29.071 --> 24:31.305
- Everyone feeling okay?

24:31.340 --> 24:33.007
- Yeah.

24:51.527 --> 24:55.429
-<i> The hallways seemed to go on</i>
<i> forever.</i>

24:58.100 --> 25:00.834
[meter beeping]

25:00.870 --> 25:03.003
[beeping rapidly]

25:03.039 --> 25:04.505
- It's picking something up.

25:04.540 --> 25:06.006
[beeping rapidly]

25:06.042 --> 25:07.408
- What is that?

25:07.443 --> 25:09.543
<i> - I looked down at the</i>
<i> K-2 meter I was holding.</i>

25:09.578 --> 25:11.478
There was lights going off
on it.

25:11.514 --> 25:15.015
[beeping rapidly]

25:15.051 --> 25:16.383
- What is it, man?

25:16.419 --> 25:19.353
[beeping slows]

25:20.856 --> 25:23.524
- It's gone.

25:23.559 --> 25:25.959
- Okay, let's keep going, guys.

25:25.995 --> 25:28.762
Nice and slowly.

25:28.798 --> 25:31.732
[high-pitched whine]

25:35.838 --> 25:38.205
Just watch your step
a little bit.

25:38.240 --> 25:40.174
- Oh, wow.

25:46.048 --> 25:49.483
- Wow, it's 11:17,
and we in something

25:49.518 --> 25:52.719
that looks kind of like a lab.

25:55.091 --> 25:57.024
- Robin, shine the light
over here, will ya?

26:00.029 --> 26:01.695
- That good?

26:13.542 --> 26:15.075
[insects chitter]
- Ugh!

26:15.111 --> 26:19.046
[insects squealing]

26:19.081 --> 26:21.615
- Just a bug.

26:34.029 --> 26:37.831
-<i> My heart started racing.</i>

26:37.867 --> 26:42.302
- Robin, what are you feeling?

26:42.338 --> 26:43.804
- It was a very nervous feeling.

26:43.839 --> 26:46.140
- Guys, watch your backs.

26:46.175 --> 26:49.176
- I felt like something bad
was about to happen.

26:49.211 --> 26:51.345
- I can feel a presence here.

26:51.380 --> 26:54.615
- What kind of presence?

26:54.650 --> 26:57.885
- I'm not sure, but I'm
definitely sensing something.

26:57.920 --> 27:01.622
<i> - It was just so overwhelming,</i>
<i> and I was a little bit shaky,</i>

27:01.657 --> 27:03.423
and that, honestly,
had never happened to me

27:03.459 --> 27:04.558
anywhere else.

27:04.593 --> 27:11.532
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:16.605 --> 27:19.206
- Most of the time,
we're using the infrared lights,

27:19.241 --> 27:21.675
<i> night vision.</i>

27:21.710 --> 27:22.843
- I want you guys

27:22.878 --> 27:23.977
to turn off your flashlights

27:24.013 --> 27:26.413
and walk as quietly
as possible.

27:26.448 --> 27:27.581
You got that?

27:27.616 --> 27:31.418
- Yeah.
- Okay. Stay together.

27:31.453 --> 27:33.720
-<i> So it's very dark.</i>

27:33.756 --> 27:35.355
You're not knowing
what you're seeing,

27:35.391 --> 27:36.390
what you're walking into.

27:36.425 --> 27:40.761
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:40.796 --> 27:43.764
[high-pitched trilling]

27:43.799 --> 27:50.737
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:56.645 --> 27:57.611
[clatter]
- [shrieks]

27:57.646 --> 28:01.215
- Oh, my God.
- What was that?

28:01.250 --> 28:03.684
Anybody want these?
- Just stay close.

28:03.719 --> 28:05.018
- Jennifer, you okay?

28:05.054 --> 28:06.053
- Yeah, yeah, it's nothing.

28:06.088 --> 28:09.156
- Okay.

28:09.191 --> 28:11.091
- Shh.

28:11.126 --> 28:14.094
[meter beeping]

28:14.129 --> 28:21.068
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:23.072 --> 28:24.204
- [coughing]

28:24.240 --> 28:25.606
- Shannon started choking.

28:25.641 --> 28:27.407
It was like she was
having trouble breathing.

28:27.443 --> 28:28.775
- [choking]
- Shannon?

28:28.811 --> 28:30.277
- Oh, my God!
- Shannon's choking.

28:30.312 --> 28:32.613
- [choking]
[indistinct chatter]

28:32.648 --> 28:34.214
[meter beeps rapidly]

28:34.250 --> 28:36.183
- You'll be okay.
- [choking]

28:36.218 --> 28:37.851
- I was worried there was
something seriously wrong.

28:37.886 --> 28:39.419
[meter beeping rapidly]
- You'll be okay.

28:39.455 --> 28:41.555
It'll be okay.
- [gasping]

28:49.031 --> 28:50.998
<i> [haunting music]</i>

28:51.033 --> 28:53.967
- [choking and coughing]

28:56.872 --> 28:59.740
- All of a sudden, it was gone,
and I could breathe again.

28:59.775 --> 29:02.709
- [breathing heavily]
- Come on, breathe.

29:10.719 --> 29:12.286
- Robin?

29:12.321 --> 29:14.888
- I realized
that I didn't see Robin.

29:14.923 --> 29:16.456
- Where's Robin?

29:18.360 --> 29:20.661
- I don't know.

29:20.696 --> 29:22.896
Any of you guys seen her?

29:22.931 --> 29:24.931
Anybody seen Robin?

29:24.967 --> 29:26.166
- I was so focused on Shannon,

29:26.201 --> 29:27.801
I didn't realize
that Robin was missing.

29:27.836 --> 29:30.470
<i> [ominous music]</i>

29:30.506 --> 29:31.805
- Robin?

29:31.840 --> 29:33.774
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:47.723 --> 29:51.692
- [panting]

29:51.727 --> 29:54.661
[footsteps pattering]

29:57.466 --> 30:01.268
<i> - Shannon was choking,</i>
<i> so I ran back to base camp</i>

30:01.303 --> 30:03.203
to get her some water
to see if that would help.

30:03.238 --> 30:10.210
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:10.245 --> 30:12.879
<i> I'm just kind of rumbling</i>
<i> through everybody's stuff,</i>

30:12.915 --> 30:15.482
<i> trying to find</i>
<i> a bottle of water.</i>

30:27.596 --> 30:29.563
[low growling sound]

30:29.598 --> 30:32.065
<i> Suddenly, I hear</i>
<i> this hissing sound</i>

30:32.101 --> 30:33.133
<i> behind my head.</i>

30:33.168 --> 30:35.969
[hissing]

30:36.004 --> 30:37.971
<i> [intense suspenseful music]</i>

30:38.006 --> 30:39.272
- [shrieking]

30:42.711 --> 30:49.649
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:52.421 --> 30:54.521
- Robin shouldn't be going off
on her own.

30:54.556 --> 30:57.324
- Yeah, she's a crazy chick,
man, a real free spirit.

30:57.359 --> 30:59.092
- Shh.
Shut up.

30:59.128 --> 31:01.428
- What?
What is it?

31:01.463 --> 31:03.096
- Did you hear that?

31:03.132 --> 31:05.932
- Suddenly, I heard
this dull creaking sound.

31:05.968 --> 31:08.902
[creaking noise]

31:20.749 --> 31:23.550
<i> I couldn't believe</i>
<i> what I was seeing.</i>

31:23.585 --> 31:25.852
The door just started to move
on its own.

31:25.888 --> 31:28.522
[door creaking]

31:28.557 --> 31:30.757
- [whispering] Shannon.

31:30.793 --> 31:34.194
You got to get down
to the basement right now.

31:34.229 --> 31:35.695
You got to see this.

31:50.078 --> 31:51.511
- What's going on?

31:57.519 --> 32:02.155
-<i> We were in shock</i>
<i> that this was happening.</i>

32:02.191 --> 32:05.125
The door opening and closing
repeatedly.

32:05.160 --> 32:07.961
[door creaking]

32:07.996 --> 32:11.465
- How's it doing that?

32:11.500 --> 32:14.701
Is there a draft somewhere?
Or a window open?

32:16.271 --> 32:19.072
- There's no windows.

32:19.107 --> 32:20.240
We're in the basement.

32:23.412 --> 32:25.545
[footsteps pounding]

32:25.581 --> 32:26.880
- Shh!

32:26.915 --> 32:27.848
Stop.

32:37.526 --> 32:38.692
[door slams]
- [shrieks]

32:38.727 --> 32:40.894
- All of a sudden, boom.

32:40.929 --> 32:43.430
[doors banging]

32:43.465 --> 32:46.733
- These doors were just openin'
and closin' and slammin'.

32:46.768 --> 32:49.736
<i> [fast-paced percussive music]</i>

32:49.771 --> 32:56.309
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:59.181 --> 33:01.982
- Ah, I think I--
I think I hear a noise.

33:04.186 --> 33:07.988
[distant whirring]

33:08.023 --> 33:10.657
[banging and whirring]

33:10.692 --> 33:12.459
Kind of scary down here.

33:15.998 --> 33:18.098
[indistinct]

33:24.806 --> 33:27.440
Okay, it's, uh,

33:27.476 --> 33:29.609
it's 21 minutes
after midnight.

33:29.645 --> 33:31.611
And, uh,

33:31.647 --> 33:34.381
down here in the basement.

33:38.220 --> 33:41.187
[whirring noise]

33:43.058 --> 33:45.225
<i> - I could hear this motor.</i>

33:45.260 --> 33:47.694
I could hear cables,
you know, grinding.

33:47.729 --> 33:50.664
[whirring]

33:53.135 --> 33:54.668
<i> This is weird, because,</i>

33:54.703 --> 33:58.238
you know, there's no power
in this place.

33:58.273 --> 34:00.907
Coming from the elevator.

34:00.943 --> 34:03.243
[bang, whirring]

34:03.278 --> 34:06.246
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

34:06.281 --> 34:08.248
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:12.220 --> 34:13.987
- Cody?

34:15.424 --> 34:17.691
Cody?

34:23.765 --> 34:25.031
- You okay?

34:26.335 --> 34:27.634
What's wrong, baby girl?

34:27.669 --> 34:29.636
- I just feel ill.

34:29.671 --> 34:30.971
- Just sit down.

34:31.006 --> 34:33.607
- I feel like I'm spinning.
- Sit down.

34:33.642 --> 34:35.942
